  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI was running lighthouse beacon node and validator 2.0.1 in ubuntu 20.04. I downloaded the last release as usual (lighthouse-v2.1.1-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.tar.gz) after that I stop the services lighthouse validator and lighthouse beacon in that order, I update the executable and relaunch again: first lighthouse beacon and then lighthouse validator.\r\n\r\nThe beacon validator seems to be running correctly, but beacon node fails.\r\n\r\n```\r\nINFO Data directory initialised              datadir: /var/lib/lighthouse\r\nWARN Running HTTP server on port 5052\r\nINFO Deposit contract                        address: 0x00000000219ab540356cbb839cbe05303d7705fa, deploy_block: 11184524\r\nWARN Unable to migrate to database schema 7, re-initializing fork choice, error: SchemaMigrationError(\"BeaconStateError(MissingBeaconBlock(SignedBeaconBlockHash(0x277b6a464a43abcc5f1a2c69f59fae1f5f894719e860f3fdbc14dcb6278a9575)))\")\r\nCRIT Failed to start beacon node             reason: Unable to open database: SchemaMigrationError(\"Missing anchor beacon state\")\r\nINFO Internal shutdown received              reason: Failed to start beacon node\r\nINFO Shutting down..                         reason: Failure(\"Failed to start beacon node\")\r\n\r\n``` \r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthouse --version\r\nLighthouse v2.1.1-5f628a7\r\nBLS library: blst-modern\r\nSHA256 hardware acceleration: false\r\nSpecs: mainnet (true), minimal (false)\r\n\r\n```\r\nWhat should I do? ",
